review_blob: Nice sharp opening, followed by a bitter kick, and a pleasant finish that continues to satisfy in the continuum.
While this may be a delightful recipe, the mixture doesnt sit nicely against the backdrop.
Not overpowering on the fruity side, this ale satisfies the thirsty, and suits the savory.
The aroma triggers dessert anticipation, and the initial touch on the tongue does not disappoint. Its subtle finish doesnt overpower.
Light but right, surprisingly silky for a rich dark stout. Smooth on the tongue, tasty in the aftermath.
Beautiful, enticing, red head who fascinates and flirts, then delivers bountiful glory. Wonderful.
This beer feels like a light beer in its texture and weight. Refreshing brew for the thirsty punter, but lacking the strength needed for sippy savoring.
This beer has a modest delivery, light and crisp, with a solid aroma. Fails to excite the palate on exit however.
Lovely color is amplified by the smooth taste and sweet finish.  A delightfully night cap after a hearty meal.
The beautiful golden glow and exquisite aroma foretell a delight that doesnt quite deliver.  While the taste is solid, it doesnt quite meet expectation.  One is nice, but the second may not satisfy.
Sweet and delicious.  Light on the tongue, smooth in the mouth, with a sensational, flavor burst crescendo.
This beer is like a desert.  I has a sweet introduction, an carmel center, and a delicious afterglow.  Nice.
Subtle raspberry flavor is somewhat surprising given the robust aroma.  Very manageable for those whod rather not have fruit in their beer.
What a nice desert.  It strikes the palate with a blast of vanilla that surrenders to Porter perfection.  Nice.
Splendid.  Smooth to start, keen on the tongue, settles nicely at the finish.  Sip after sip is a pleasure.
This beer looks good, but lacks the killer kick.  its smooth on the palate, but finishes with a spoiler.
The appearance and aroma create an expectation that the flavor fails to uphold.  The beer unfortunately suffers from unrealized potential.
This beer was recommended to me.  I have to say, wonderful beer.  It hits the tongue with an attractive ease then finishes with a smooth lift.  Excellent overall quality.
